<item>
            <title>[SOLR-411] Solr JAR Packaging Names</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-411</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d like to suggest Solr migrate the way it names it&apos;s JARs to be like what is increasingly the de-facto standard for naming released JARs:&lt;br/&gt;
apache-solr-common-1.3-dev.jar&lt;br/&gt;
apache-solr-solrj-1.3-dev.jar&lt;br/&gt;
apache-solr-1.3-dev.jar&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;instead of the current way which puts the subproject after the version declaration.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch to follow that modifies the build.xml&lt;/p&gt;</description>
